Package magellan.library.tasks

Class AbstractInspector

  • java.lang.Object
    • magellan.library.tasks.AbstractInspector
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Inspector
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AttackInspector, BuildingInspector, GameDataInspector, MaintenanceInspector, MessageInspector, MovementInspector, OrderSyntaxInspector, ShipInspector, SkillInspector, TeachInspector, ToDoInspector, TransferInspector
    public abstract class AbstractInspector
extends java.lang.Object
implements Inspector
    This is an abstract implementation of an inspector. You can use this as a base for your own implementation.

      • suppress

        public Unit suppress​(Problem p)
        Description copied from interface: Inspector
        Modifies the orders such that this problem is not listed by the inspector in the future, i.e. by adding a comment to the source unit's orders. Note that it is in the responsibility of the caller to fire OrderChangedEvents.
        Specified by:
        suppress in interface Inspector
        Returns:
        Returns a unit whose orders were changed or null if this was not possible
        See Also:
        Inspector.suppress(Problem)
